Date: Sun, 16 Jul 2000 08:20:00 -0400
From: Dickson Despommier <ddd1@columbia.edu>

Comment on species of birds affected by West Nile virus
Perhaps the reason why "house "sparrows (actually the English sparrow) and
starlings appear to be immune is because they were invader species from
Europe. Just a thought, but that is probably why no European or near
eastern species of bird at the Bronx Zoo died last year. Only those from
the Americas
or the Indian subcontinent were felled by the infection, even though birds
from Africa and the Middle East were housed next to them.
--
Dickson Despommier
The Mailman School of Public Health
Columbia UNiversity
<ddd1@columbia.edu>
